<p>'The difficulty is that for the human species that's been born biological male, if they go through puberty in particular, they have, absolutely, have some physiological advantages,' she told the ABC's 7.30 program.</p>

<p>'Whether it is bone strength or extra capillarisation or larger muscle bulk, but then there are other aspects of that as well, not only does that affect performance but there is a health or a danger aspect.'</p>

<p>The issue of transgender athletes is so politically toxic Tasmanian Liberal senator Claire Chandler was labelled as 'transphobic' after calling for transgender rugby players to be banned to 'protect women's safety'.</p>

<p>Labor senator Nita Green likened Senator Chandler to Harry Potter author JK Rowling, who has angered trans activists by suggesting only someone born biologically female could understand what it was like to be a woman.</p>

